<HL>
   International Brief -- Scottish &amp; Newcastle Breweries:
   Pretax Profit for Fiscal '90
   Rose 33% to $320.6 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.SCT
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Scottish &amp; Newcastle Breweries PLC of Britain said pretax
profit for the year ended April 29 rose 33% to #183.3 million
($320.6 million) from #138.2 million a year earlier, helped
by strong gains in brewing and the company's new leisure
division.
   Profit after taxes, less minority interests and
allocations to profit-sharing and before an extraordinary
gain of #424.4 million from sales of assets, rose 27% to
#116.1 million from #91.3 million a year earlier, when the
company had an extraordinary loss of #4.8 million in
connection with successfully defending a hostile takeover
bid. Earnings per share increased 23% to 28.7 pence from 23.4
pence. Profit attributable shareholders surged to #535.5
million from #81.2 million. Operating profit rose 32% to
#210.9 million from #159.8 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales climbed 20% to #1.24 billion from #1.03 billion.
   The company is recommending a final dividend of 8.58 pence
a share, making a total payout of 13 pence, an increase of
20% from 10.83 pence a year earlier.
</TEXT>
